  "id": "MGASA-2017-0380",
  "summary": "Updated db48 and db53 packages fix security vulnerability",
  "details": "It was found that Berkeley DB reads the DB_CONFIG configuration file from the\ncurrent working directory by default. This happens when calling db_create()\nwith dbenv=NULL; or using the dbm_open() function (CVE-2017-10140).\n",
